7 Question 4 Think back to last week where we talked about wide vs long format. As the data is in wide format, its pretty clear to see we have a lot of missing values. Reshape the data from wide to long format, so that for each country the year column becomes a row. Name the column you put your values into (i.e.the values_into argument) prop_women.

 

women_in_gov_wideformat <- women_in_gov_clean %>%
  pivot_longer(cols = c("1960": "2018"), 
               names_to = "year", 
               values_to = "prop_women") 

View(women_in_gov_wideformat)
